SELECT MAX(`Percent (%) Eligible FRPM (K-12)`) AS HighestEligibleFreeRate
FROM frpm
JOIN schools ON frpm.CDSCode = schools.CDSCode
WHERE schools.`County` = 'Alameda';
1:
SELECT 
    f."School Name", 
    CAST(f."Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)" AS REAL) / f."Enrollment (Ages 5-17)" AS "Eligible Free Rate"
FROM 
    frpm AS f
INNER JOIN 
    schools AS s
ON 
    f.CDSCode = s.CDSCode
WHERE 
    s.EdOpsName = 'Continuation School'
ORDER BY 
    "Eligible Free Rate" ASC
LIMIT 3;

WITH EnrollmentDifference AS (
    SELECT
        s.CDSCode,
        s.School,
        s.DOCType,
        f.`Enrollment (K-12)` - f.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)` AS Difference
    FROM
        schools s
    INNER JOIN
        frpm f
    ON
        s.CDSCode = f.CDSCode
    WHERE
        s.FundingType = 'Locally funded'
)
SELECT
    School,
    DOCType
FROM
    EnrollmentDifference
WHERE
    Difference > (SELECT AVG(Difference) FROM EnrollmentDifference);

WITH RankedSchools AS (
    SELECT
        s.`School Name`,
        s.`Enrollment (K-12)`,
        f.`Free Meal Count (K-12)`,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY f.`Enrollment (K-12)` DESC) AS rank
    FROM
        schools s
    INNER JOIN
        frpm f
    ON
        s.CDSCode = f.CDSCode
)
SELECT
    r.`School Name`,
    r.`Enrollment (K-12)`,
    r.`Free Meal Count (K-12)`,
    r.`Eligible Free Rate (%)`
FROM
    RankedSchools r
WHERE
    r.rank <= 10
ORDER BY
    r.`Enrollment (K-12)` DESC
LIMIT
    10, 2;

WITH AdminNames AS (
    SELECT 
        AdmFName1 AS FirstName, 
        AdmLName1 AS LastName, 
        School, 
        City 
    FROM schools 
    WHERE Charter = 1 AND CharterNum = '00D2'

    UNION

    SELECT 
        AdmFName2 AS FirstName, 
        AdmLName2 AS LastName, 
        School, 
        City 
    FROM schools 
    WHERE Charter = 1 AND CharterNum = '00D2'

    UNION

    SELECT 
        AdmFName3 AS FirstName, 
        AdmLName3 AS LastName, 
        School, 
        City 
    FROM schools 
    WHERE Charter = 1 AND CharterNum = '00D2'
)
SELECT 
    School, 
    City, 
    FirstName || ' ' || LastName AS AdministratorName 
FROM AdminNames;

        WHEN P.player_name = 'Daan Smith' AND M.away_player_1 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_2 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_3 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_4 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_5 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_6 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_7 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_8 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_9 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal 
        WHEN P.player_name = 'Filipe Ferreira' AND M.away_player_10 = P.player_api_id THEN M.away_team_goal

    OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_4

    OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_6 
    OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_7 
    OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_8 
    OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_9 
    OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_10 
    OR P.player_api_id = M.away_player_11

1482:
WITH SegmentConsumption AS (
    SELECT
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2013,
        SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(y.Date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption2012
    FROM customers c
    JOIN yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE c.Currency = 'EUR' AND c.Segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')
    GROUP BY c.Segment
),
PercentageChange AS (
    SELECT
        Segment,
        Consumption2013,
        Consumption2012,
        (Consumption2013 - Consumption2012) * 100.0 / Consumption2013 AS PercentageIncrease
    FROM SegmentConsumption
    WHERE Consumption2013 > 0 -- Avoid division by zero
)
SELECT
    Segment,
    Consumption2013,
    Consumption2012,
    PercentageIncrease
FROM PercentageChange
ORDER BY PercentageIncrease DESC
LIMIT 1; -- Biggest increase
